content: Can't keep these stocks down. Some familiar names once again hitting new all-time highs. $PDD $DG $DOCU $LULU $CCI $TSCO $SPGI $LOGI $SAM among others.
Mostly quiet on the earnings front next week. But I'll be keeping an eye on results from $DKS $CRWD $ZM $CPB $AEO $CNK $GOOS $SJM $TTC $MIK $CIEN $AVGO $GPS $WORK. Plus,  the jobs report is Friday.
All-time highs for these stocks today. You'll notice a lot of familiar names. $NVDA $PDD $SPLK $TWLO $DDOG $SHOP $COUP $LULU $OKTA $MDB $SMG $CMG

Next week's a short one for traders due to Memorial Day. But still a fair amount of earnings on tap. $AZO $RL $HPQ $TOL $WDAY $BOX $DG $DLTR $NIO $ANF $COST $DELL $CRM $VMW $JWN $ULTA $WSM $OLLI $OKTA $BIG $CGC among the highlights.

Not a huge amount of earnings on tap next week. But some notable ones, especially in tech and retail. $BIDU $WMT $HD $KSS $SINA $WB $TGT $LOW $ADI $EXPE $LB $TTWO $BBY $TJX $HRL $HPE $INTU $NVDA $PANW $SPLK $DECK $BABA $DE $PDD $FL

Dunkin' Brands going one step further beyond store closures. $DNKN says it will "immediately remove tables and chairs from all restaurants and outdoor patios." $DNKN encouraging mobile ordering and delivery via $JTKWY.

More store closures. L Brands says it will "temporarily close all Bath & Body Works, Victoria’s Secret and PINK stores in the United States and Canada, effective March 17 through March 29, 2020. " $LB

Get ready for more companies to say they are "not providing guidance" due to COVID-19. Both $DBI and $PLCE did so this morning. Designer Brands also temporarily shutting shoe stores. All sales to be done online.
Cross border chip deal going through? The Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States green lit merger of Germany's Infineon and US-based Cypress. $CY up nearly 50% #premarket.
Not so fashionable. Oof. Stitch Fix cuts outlook. $SFIX plunging more than 33% #premarket.
Fundamentals still matter. Some notable earnings reports on tap next week. Pay attention for any coronavirus impact. $THO $SOHU $DKS $PDD $WUBA $DG $ORCL $AVGO $GPS $ADBE $ULTA $DOCU $WORK
Worst over for the airlines or just some bottom fishing? The broader $DJT transports index is down again. But $UAL $AAL $LUV $DAL $ALK $JBLU all solidly higher.
Solid earnings and sales from optical networking equipment company Ciena. Topped forecasts. Gaining market share from Huawei? $CIEN up 7% #premarket.

Earnings on Monday from China's $JD. What will company say about coronavirus? Also on tap to report next week? $TGT $KSS $AZO $HPE $JWN $URBN $ROST $DLTR $CPB $BF.B $ANF $AEO $ZM $KR $TECD $BJ $CIEN $BURL $KTB $COST $HRB $FNKO $AOBC. A LOT of consumer stocks. And jobs report!
Not ready for the $BIG time. Oof. Big Lots is the latest retailer to warn of coronavirus-related supply disruptions in China. Missed on earnings and revs. $BIG down 20%.
Solid sales not enough for Beyond Meat. Investors hungry for actual profits too. $BYND down more than 11% #premarket.
Go jump in a $LAKE? Hazmat suit maker Lakeland continues to surge on coronavirus fears. This happened during Ebola scare too. $LAKE up 24% #premarket following more than 20% spike yesterday.
Beyond Meat posts a loss but sales beat. Will it matter in this market? $BYND down 4% after hours.
Add AB InBev to the  list of companies warning about a coronavirus hit. $BUD down nearly 9% #premarket after the beer giant's outlook disappointed.
Solid earnings forecast from Square. Cash App booming. Now has 24  million users. $SQ up more than 4% #premarket.
Is SmileDirectClub the worst IPO of the past few years? $SDC down nearly 25% #premarket after lousy earnings. Stock around $8.70. Went public last year at $23.
Salesforce down 1% #premarket despite earnings beat. Surprise departure of $CRM co-CEO Keith Block. It's solely the Benioff show now. Also announced $1.3B deal for Vlocity.
Teladoc to get a boost from coronavirus outbreak? The director of CDC’s National Center for Immunization and Respiratory Diseases said hospitals should boost telehealth services. $TDOC up 4%.
Palo Alto has been red hot. Riding the cybersecurity wave. But sales missed. Guidance weak. Momentum is fickle. $PANW down 15% #premarket.

Macy's finally turning things around? Earnings beat for its holiday quarter. So did sales -- although they were still down slightly from a year ago. $M up about 1% #premarket. Let's see if that holds.
Housing market continues to show signs of strength. And that's good news for Home Depot. Solid earnings bet. $HD up more than 2% #premarket.

The earnings "season" is winding down. But keep an eye out next week for results from $HPQ $INTU $HTZGQ $PANW $HD $M $CRM $SPCE LOW $TJX $SJM $SINA $WB $WEN $PZZA $SEAS $MAR $LB $BKNG $SQ $BBY $BUD $JCP $KDP $DELL $BIDU $VMW $LYV $MNST $AMC $WDAY $BYND $W $FL among others.

The market is closed Monday for Presidents' Day. But the earnings calendar is still chock full of results from top companies. $WMT $MDT $BLMN $DISH $ADI $H $CAKE $ZG $CAR $PARA $DPZ $ED $DE $CNK and many more.
Expedia soaring after solid earnings and a healthy forecast. $EXPE up 12% #premarket. Keep an eye on $BKNG and $TRIP today too.
Mattel earnings topped forecasts. $MAT up 2% #premarket. Still, these are challenging times for toymakers. See $HAS $FNKO
Cord cutting helping Roku. Strong earnings and revenue as the streaming revolution continues. $ROKU up 8% #premarket.
Nvidia is surging thanks to strong data center revenue powering earnings. $NVDA up 6% #premarket.

Cannabis stocks should fly high (sorry) today. Smaller loss than expected for Canopy Growth. Sales beat. $CGC up 20% #premarket. Should be good news for Canopy investor $STZ too. And rival pot stocks $CRON $APHA $ACB $TLRY soaring as well.

Wall Street's final frontier? Branson's Virgin Galactic continues to orbit well above the rest of the market. $SPCE SPAC up 6% today and more than 110% YTD! Makes you wonder how SpaceX could do if Musk ever took it public.
Kraft Heinz sales continue to fall and missed forecasts. Earnings did beat but $KHC down more than 1% #premarket.
No dips for chips today? Solid earnings and outlook from semiconductor equipment giant Applied Materials. $AMAT up 2.5% #premarket.
Pepsi beat on earnings and revenue. Guidance looks to be a touch light though. Boosts dividend. Will be interesting to see what $PEP stock does today.
Cisco earnings beat but sales missed. Outlook weak. China IT environment sluggish due to coronavirus. $CSCO down 5% #premarket.

Bad news for NY sports fans? $MSGE president on conference call. Despite their lousy records, "the Knicks and Rangers consistently ranked in the top 3 for ticket sales in both the NBA and NHL, which drove steady ticket-related revenue for the second quarter."

Earnings season starting to wind down a bit. But still plenty of noteworthy results on tap next week. $QSR $HLT $HAS $UAA $LYFT $CVS $TEVA $TAP $SHOP $CSCO $AMAT $MGM $ATUS $BAB $PEP $KHC $NVDA $EXPE $MAT $ROKU $YELP and many more.
Unplugged? Or what goes up must go down? $TSLA down another 5% #premarket. Hovering around the $700 level.

Earnings parade continues next week. $GOOGL $SNE $BP $F $DIS $PRU $ALL $AFL $CMG $SNAP $MTCH $GM $MRK $SPOT $MET $QCOM $FOX $IAC $JTKWY $CI $STLA $TSN $YUM $TWTR.P $DNKN $UBER $BIDU $ATVI $PINS $ABBV (I own the latter.) Will anyone care about results or will it be all coronavirus?

A LOT of earnings next week. $DHI $ARNC $WHR $JNPR $FFIV $RTX $LMT $HCA $PFE $MMM $SAP $XRX $HOG $AAPL $SBUX $EBAY $AMD CNN owner $T $ELV $GE $BA $GD $DOW $MCD $MA $MSFT $META $TSLA $MDLZ $PYPL $LVS $VZ $UPS $KO $NOC $MO $AMZN $V $EA $AMGN $XOM $CVX $CAT + many more & the Fed!
Broader market higher but coronavirus concerns hitting companies with exposure to Chinese consumer. $LKNCY $YUMC $MGM $WYNN $LVS $BABA $BIDU all in red.
Paycom gets an index bump. $PAYC up 4.5% after S&P says it will add it to the $SPX. Company replacing health insurer $WCG, which is getting acquired by rival Centene. $CNC already in the index.
Time to see which biotech will be able to treat the coronavirus effectively? Gilead Sciences up to highs of the day on reports suggesting $GILD could use an Ebola drug to combat the disease.
Coronavirus fears are back and casino investors are nervous. $WYNN $MGM $LVS $MLCO all down notably #premarket. All have big presence in Macau.
Swiss miss? UBS results did top forecasts but the bank's outlook is lower than expected. $UBS down 4% #premarket.

Market closed Monday for MLK Day. But it's still a busy week for earnings over the next four days. On tap? $HAL $IBM $COF $UAL $NFLX $JNJ $TXN $CMCSA $PG $AAL $TRV $LUV $UNP $KMB $JBLU $INTC $ETFC $AXP and many more.

Come out and $PLAY! Dave & Buster's up nearly 15% after $KKR affiliate discloses 6.3% activist stake and says it has already had and intends "to continue to engage in discussions with management" about its business strategy.
Another parade of blue chips hitting all-time highs today along with broader market. $AMD $MSFT $V $META $PG $MA $LLY $MDT $UNP $SO $BRK.B $AXP $ALL $GOOGL $LMT. And many more.
Blind Mellon. $BK is the worst performing stock in the S&P 500 today following weak revenue. BNY Mellon down nearly 8%.
Maybe Musk meant he had funding secured at $520? Tesla stock continues its electric streak. $TSLA up 6% today to near $509.
Cannabis stocks surging today. Any news? Not seeing any. But $CRON $CGC $TLRY $APHA all sharply higher. $APHA earnings are out tomorrow morning.
Namaste! Lululemon raises its earnings and revenue guidance for Q4. $LULU up more than 2% #premarket.
Earnings season is upon us. Finally! Results due out next week from $JPM $WFC $C $DAL $APHA $UNH $GS $BAC $USB $PNC $BLK $AA $MS $BK $TSM $PPG $CSX $SLB $STT $JBHT $RF $CFG $KSU
Apple stock at a new all-time high. $AAPL just needs to go up about $100 more until it's trading at today's magic number. $409.
Brutal holiday sales figures for JCPenny. Sorry. I meant JCPenney. Same-store sales down 7.5% but "only" dropped 5.3% when you adjust for their exit from appliance and furniture. $JCP at $1.20.
It wasn't a Merry Christmas for Kohl's. Despite a buzzy partnership with $AMZN, same-store sales at Kohl's fell during the holidays. Forecasts EPS at low end of guidance too. $KSS down 6% #premarket.

New Year's weight loss resolutions finally kicking in? $WW (formerly Weight Watchers) fell more than 7% Tuesday but it's been surging since then. Up another 9% today and now up nearly 18% so far in 2020.
Time for a Corona? And some cannabis? Constellation Brands beat on earnings. $STZ up 3% #premarket.
Macy's is down, but not out? Struggling retailer reported a drop in same-store sales for November and December. But not as bad as feared. $M up nearly 4% #premarket.
Tesla is on a tear. $TSLA up another 2% #premraket -- to above $460.
Finally a reason to smile for SmileDirectClub investors? $SDC has been an IPO flop so far. But $SDC shares up nearly 9% #premarket after the company announced distribution deal with Walmart. $WMT 😃

Iran concerns really rattling investors in airlines, truckers and railroads as oil spikes. All 20 stocks in the $DJT -- referring to Dow Jones Transports, not Donald J. You Know Who -- are lower today. Biggest losers? Airlines $AAL $UAL $ALK $JBLU and auto rental giant $CAR.
Overall market still lower but some cybersecurity stocks up on Iran worries. $CIBR $IHAK $BUG and $HACK ETFs up slightly. $FTNT $ZS $MNDT $CRWD $CYBR all modestly higher.
Not a lot on the calendar next week. Still feels like the holiday hangover hasn't ended yet. But keep eye on earnings from $WBA $LEN $STZ $BBBYQ $KBH. And the December jobs report on Friday morning.
$TSLA up nearly 4% today on strong deliveries numbers. Stock now trading around $446 -- which is 6% higher than the "funding secured" levels if you're keeping score at home.
Lots of familiar names topping the all-time highs list to kick of 2020. $AMD $AAPL $MSFT $BABA $JPM $V $MA $RTX $ADBE $UNP
BlackBerry beat on earnings and sales. But waiting for guidance. So far so good though. $BB up 8% #premarket.
Looks like someone needs Amazon after all. FedEx missed on earnings and sales. Lowers outlook. $FDX down nearly 4% after hours.

FedEx down just 1% today despite $AMZN competition concerns. But earnings after the close. Been a tough year. $FDX flat in 2019. Missing market rally. Lagging $UPS too. Big Brown up nearly 25% this year.
This is what it sounds like when the maker of Dove cries. Unilever warns on sales. $UN $UL down 6% #premarket.

Market in rally mode again today. All-time highs for many blue chips, including $AAPL $MSFT $JPM $NKE $USB $PG $UNH $TGT $BBY $ADBE $MA $UNP $BRK.B $MDT $UNP $HUM $RTX $QRVO $AMGN $HLT $ACN $H $MCO $GOOGL and many more.
Next week is the week before Christmas and not many bulls or bears will be stirring. Just a handful of earnings worth noting on tap. $FDX $GIS $ACN $RAD $CAG $DRI $NKE $KMX $BB
One out of four ain't bad? A quartet of earnings last night. But of that group, only $ADBE is up #premarket. $ORCL $AVGO $COST all pointing to lower opens.
$CIEN is one of the holdings in the relatively new $FIVG ETF. Going to be talking to the people behind that and write story early next week about it.
$CIEN CEO Smith told me that the global rollout of 5G is beginning and is very important for Ciena. Positive dynamic for next few years. $CIEN is supplier to $TMUS $VZ and CNN owner $T.
$CIEN CEO Smith on Huawei. Said some telecom customers have concerns about overdependence on China. That is an opportunity for Ciena over next few years.
Talking to Ciena CEO Gary Smith about earnings and guidance. $CIEN now up 12%. Says innovation driving performance. Strong outlook for the quarter and year.
Ciena missed on earnings. $CIEN  down 4% #premarket. Talking to Ciena CEO Gary Smith later this morning about the quarter and outlook.
The earnings calendar is very light next week. But stay tuned for results from $TOL $CHWY $SFIX $AZO $GME $PLAY $AEO $PLCE $LULU $TLRD $CIEN $COST $ORCL $ADBE $AVGO
It's all about expectations. Apparel retailers Express and J.Jill both reported drops in sales. But Express topped forecasts and J.Jill didn't. $EXPR up 12% #premarket and $JILL down 27%.

Shopify is a good company. But is it really a takeover target? $SHOP up 6% after Cramer apparently said on CNBC tech firms were looking at it. Still, not sure anyone would buy $SHOP at a nearly $45B market cap (before any premium) and a 2020 P/E ratio of over 400!

Apache probably wishing it took takeover offer from Anadarko back in 2015. $APA down another 6% today after plunging 12% Monday. Apache at nearly 20-year low after the company gave very little new info in an update about oil well off the coast of Suriname. 🛢️

Cord cutting is real but Morgan Stanley has suddenly turned bearish on Roku. $MS downgrades $ROKU to underweight and cuts price target to $110 -- more than 30% below current price. $ROKU down 6.5% #premarket.
Earnings calendar is extremely light next week. But I'll be keeping an eye on $LE $CRM $WDAY $BNED $CPB $RH $WORK $KR $TD $DG $MIK $SIG $TIF $BF.B $ULTA $BIG. Plus, the jobs report is next Friday.
Looks like it might be a happy Black Friday, Cyber Monday and holiday shopping season in general for Best Buy. Beat on earnings and sales. Raises outlook. $BBY up nearly 6% #premarket.
Earnings calendar is light for the Thanksgiving shortened week ahead. But results due out from $A $HPE $PVH $PANW $BBY $DLTR $HRL $ADI $ANF $DEL $HPQ $VMW $GES $BOX $DE 🙏🦃🏈🛍️
Mind the Gap? Struggling retailer reported earnings and sales that topped forecasts and interim CEO says Gap still on track to spin off Old Navy. $GPS up 4% #premarket.

Good sign for Nike and other sneaker/athletic equipment companies? Both Foot Locker and Hibbett reported solid earnings and same-store sales this morning. $FL up 4% #premarket. $HIBB soaring 22% . $NKE up nearly 1%. 👟
Department store blues. Weak outlook for Kohl's may be the $KSS of death for other struggling retailers. Macy's and Nordstrom tumbling #premarket too. $M and $JWN both down 5%.

Not a lot of earnings next week. Most companies have reported. But I'll be watching $MANU $HD $TJX $KSS $MDT $URBN $TGT $LOW $PD $LB $M $GPS $JWN $INTU $POST $WSM $SJM $FL. Did I miss any others of note?
More bad news for cannabis stocks. Aurora missed on sales. $ACB plunges 11% #premarket. $CGC $CRON $TLRY $APHA all down again too.
China consumer holding up okay? $JD beat on revenue. Stock up 4% #premarket. $BABA has momentum too. Solid, if not spectacular, sales growth for Singles Day earlier this week as well.
Department stores aren't dead? Yet? Dillards posts an unexpected profit. $DDS up 8% #premarket. But overall revenue down and same-store sales flat.
Chinese social media firm Weibo missed on sales and investors not happy. $WB down 10% #premarket and that's weighing on Weibo parent Sina as well. $SINA down 4%.
Smiley faces in Arkansas and on Wall Street. Walmart beat on earnings. Sales roughly in line. Raised outlook. $WMT up 3% #premarket.

Bigger loss for cannabis company Canopy Growth and revs missed too. $CGC down nearly 7% #premarket. Keep an eye on big Canopy backer Constellation Brands $STZ today too. As well as rival pot stocks $CRON $APHA $ACB $TLRY
Nothing seems to be going right for Altria. $MO has a big Juul problem and Cronos, the Canadian cannabis company that Altria has a stake in, missed on sales this morning. $CRON down more than 3%.
More woes for online retail/blockchain company Overstock. Missed on earnings and revs. $OSTK down 4% #premarket. Near 52-week low.
Do cry over spilled milk? Dairy company Dean Foods files for bankruptcy. $DF is a penny stock. 80 cents a share. prnewswire.com/news-release...

This Kona, Redhook and Widmer Brothers are for you. AB InBev already owns 31% of Craft Brew Alliance. $BUD now paying $16.50 a share to buy rest of the company. Giant premium. $BREW up 122.5% #premarket. 🍺🍻

Earnings "season" is almost over. But some notable results still due out next week. $TME $TSN $CBS $OSTK $CRON $SDC $GOOS $LKNCY $CSCO $NTAP $WMT $BAM $PARA $SINA $WB $CGC $AMAT $NVDA $JD $JCP and a bunch more.
SeaWorld has a new CEO. Again. But investors giving the troubled company the benefit of the doubt -- even though it reported earnings and sales that missed forecasts. $SEAS up more than 10%.
No wreck-it Ralph after $RL earnings. Ralph Lauren tops forecasts. $RL up nearly 10% #premarket.
Expedia missed on earnings and lowered guidance. Analysts cutting ratings and price targets. $EXPE down 13% #premarket.
Satellite TV not dead yet? $DISH up 7% #premarket after earnings and revs topped forecasts and company posted surprise subscriber growth. (Disclosure. CNN parent $T owns Dish rival DirecTV.)
Square beat on earnings. Guidance looks a little weak, but that's adjusted for sale of Caviar biz to DoorDash. Investors seem okay with it. $SQ up more than 1% after hours.
Big bleeping Q! Qualcomm tops forecasts. Solid outlook. $QCOM up 4% after hours.
Looking for love in all the wrong places. Match earnings fail to impress. Outlook is light. $MTCH down 12% after hours. Company says it will evaluate proposal for full spin-off from $IAC.
Pretty violent reaction to slight miss on sales by Weight Watchers. $WW down 16% after hours. But it beat on earnings and raised outlook.
The lowest price for $UBER since the IPO was $28.31. Keep an eye on that today. $UBER currently down 7% #premarket following earnings...to $28.95.
No clouds in the sky for Adobe. Software giant beat on earnings. Healthy guidance. $ADBE up nearly 5% #premarket.
Turnaround Tuesday? Two struggling retailers posted profits that topped forecasts. Coach owner Tapestry and supermarket king Kroger. Both $TPR and $KR up #premarket.
Uber "earnings" after the close. Traders don't seem too optimistic after $LYFT tanked on results last week. $UBER down 2.5%. Stock just 8% above all-time low.

The frantic pace of earnings reports is slowing. But still plenty on tap next week. $SYY $UAA $RACE $PRU $MAR $UBER $ARNC $TPR $DVA $CZR $CVS $HUM $PZZA $NYT $QCOM $BIDU $WYNN $ABC $CAH $KDP $RL $AMC $KTB $DIS $BKNG $NWSA $SYMC $ATVI $TTWO and many more. What did I miss?
Going to try and leave shortly after the closing bell to trick or treat with the kids. But if you're sticking around, keep an eye on earnings from $LYV $X $CAR $QRVO $PINS $FNKO
Mmm. Donuts. Dunkin' may have missed on same-store sales. But it beat on earnings. $DNKN up 5%. 🍩☕️
Bigger than expected loss for Wayfair. $W down 8% #premarket. When will Wayfair ever be profitable?
Sales down at Kraft Heinz and they were slightly below forecasts -- despite price increases in several products. But earnings beat. $KHC up nearly 6% #premarket.

Yum! Brands missed on earnings. $YUM down 5%. Is the KFC/Pizza Hut/Taco Bell owner's stake in troubled GrubHub a problem too? $YUM invested $200M last year. $JTKWY plunged 43% yesterday after earnings.
One word. Plastics. Okay. Two words. Plastic shoes. Crox beat on earnings and revenue. Solid outlook. $CROX up 5% #premarket.

Molson Coors cutting 400 to 500 jobs and looks to move beyond beer (not to be confused with Beyond Meat). Company changing name to Molson Coors Beverage. Used to be Brewing. BTW, it missed on sales and earnings too. $TAP down 2% #premarket.
Walgreens beat on earnings but these are still tough times for $WBA and top rival $CVS.
See $SPOT soar. Surprise profit for Spotify on solid subscription growth. Take that, $AAPL? $SPOT up 8% #premarket.
Burger King's Impossible Whoppers and the Popeyes super popular chicken sandwich fuel strong sales and earnings at Restaurant Brands. $QSR

Revenge of the JEDI. In a big snub for Amazon, Microsoft wins key $10B Pentagon cloud defense contract. $MSFT up more than 3% #premarket. $AMZN down 1%. Could $MSFT move back ahead of Apple for top market cap today? $AAPL up slightly.

Tesla up another 9% today after yesterday's earnings surprise. $TSLA now down only about 1.5% for the year. Will it soon be back in black for 2019? Still more than 15% below the $387.46 price it topped out at in August '18 after Musk's "funding secured" tweet.

No rest next week. Earnings from CNN owner $T $WBA $SPOT $QSR $BYND $GOOGL $TMUS $BP $GM $PFE $MRK $MA $K $MDLZ $YUMC $MAT $EA $SNE $GE $YUM $AAPL $META $SBUX $MET $CI $STLA $DD $KHC $WWE $DNKN $YETI $BABA $XOM $CVX. And many more. And the Fed on Wednesday. And jobs report Friday!
More California fires = bigger problems for troubled electric company PG&E. $PCG down 30% #premarket.
Vans no longer as cool as they once were? VF Corp. missed on earnings. And Vans sales are slowing. Vans revenue up 14% in the quarter, compared to 26% a year ago. $VFC down 5% #premarket.
Verizon earnings top forecasts. Revs beat slightly too. Reaffirms outlook. $VZ up 1% #premarket.
AB InBev missed on earnings and revenue. Problems in China. Hmm. That seems like a theme this quarter. $BUD down 9% #premarket.
Amazon missed on earnings. Guidance not great. $AMZN down more than 6% after hours so far. No Bezos evil cackling GIF today.

Smile! Invisalign owner Align Technology investors are grinning from ear to ear after solid earnings. $ALGN up 15%. Helping to boost SmileDirectClub too? $SDC up 7%. But still more than 50% below $23 IPO price.

Canadian cannabis company Tilray popping today after company said its medical marijuana was imported to US for part of a clinical trial for breast cancer patients suffering from peripheral neuropathy. $TLRY up more than 7%.
How about $NOW? The ServiceNow slide after CEO said he was leaving to take job at $NKE was short-lived. Solid earnings. $NOW up 8%.
Just say no to Nokia? Tough competition and higher costs from 5G deployment is hurting $NOK. The Finnish telecom equipment company cut outlook and suspended dividend. $NOK down nearly 20% #premarket.
A Roomba won't be able to clean up this mess. iRobot tanking on weak outlook. $IRBT down 18.5% #premarket.
ServiceNow CEO leaves to take Nike job. And ServiceNow replaces John Donahoe with Bill McDermott, former head of SAP. Whew. $NOW down 8% #premarket. $NKE flat.
Boeing earnings unsurprisingly  missed due to more 737 Max woes. But sales a little better than forecast. Investors breathe a sigh of relief? $BA up 1% #premarket.
Chipotle down 3% today. Earnings after the close. Concerns following $MCD miss and same-store sales slowdown? $CMG still up more than 90% YTD though.
Snapchat "earnings" after the close. $SNAP down 3% today but it soared 8% yesterday and is up 156% YTD. So expectations might be unreasonably high? Especially with $META/Insta still copying it?
McDonald's missed on earnings and same store sales growth a bit disappointing too. $MCD down 3% #premarket.
A lot of earnings so far but futures mostly flat/slightly higher. But good numbers from $LMT $PG $HOG. Not so much from $HAS $TRV $UPS. Waiting for $MCD.

Rest this weekend. A LOT of earnings next week. On tap? $SAP $HAL $AMTD $UPS $RTX $PG $TRV $LMT $MCD $KMB $JBLU $HAS $HOG $WHR $CMG $TXN $SNAP $ELV $BA $CAT $CMCSA $AAL $DOW $MMM $LUV $NOC $HSY $TWTR.P $AMZN $INTC $COF $V $VZ $BUD and many many more. Whew! What did I miss?

Don't leave home without it? AmEx beat on earning and sales and reaffirms guidance. $AXP up 2% #premarket.
Coke beats on sales. Meets on earnings. Good enough? $KO up more than 1% #premarket.

#StupidStock Move of the Day! Surprised to see cannabis stock Aphria fall back this hard after earnings euphoria lifted it nearly 25% yesterday. $APHA down 7.5% today but it did post profit. Rivals $CGC $ACB down just 1%. $CRON $TLRY actually up.
Slack continues to be a slacker of a stock. Latest bit of bad news? Morgan Stanley is losing faith. $MS slashed $WORK target from $38 to $28. $WORK down 6% -- to just above $23.
Storm clouds gathering for Workday? Investors seem unimpressed by yesterday's analyst and customer presentations. $WDAY down 11%.

BofA/ML really likes Nvidia. $NVDA up 5% after $BAC raised price target on the graphics chip maker to $250. That's more than 25% above the current price and is highest target among mainstream Wall Street firms.
$PINS and needles. PInterest down about 3% after IPO lockup period expires. Still, Pinterest has fared a lot better than other recent unicorn IPOs like $UBER $LYFT $WORK, etc.
